377
00:41:39,480 --> 00:41:42,480
But we can get him on
income tax evasion if we can show

378
00:41:42,690 --> 00:41:46,820
that any of the 'organisation'
business money is going to him.

379
00:41:47,030 --> 00:41:51,240
- Legally, he receives no income.
- He doesn't receive anything?

380
00:41:51,450 --> 00:41:55,000
- Mr Ness? You have a visitor.
- Mister Ness!

381
00:41:55,200 --> 00:41:58,290
Could we talk for a minute?
I'm John O'Shea, Alderman...

382
00:41:58,500 --> 00:42:00,380
Yes, I know who you are.

383
00:42:03,300 --> 00:42:06,010
Would you excuse us?

384
00:42:08,010 --> 00:42:11,930
We are busy with several large
operations. What can I do for you?

385
00:42:12,140 --> 00:42:15,350
I came up to congratulate you
on a job well done.

386
00:42:17,020 --> 00:42:21,310
Share your good fortune
on such a lovely day.

387
00:42:25,110 --> 00:42:26,740
What's that?

388
00:42:31,700 --> 00:42:34,700
- What is that?
- Mr Ness, you're an educated man.

389
00:42:34,910 --> 00:42:38,370
Let me pay you the compliment
of being blunt.

390
00:42:38,580 --> 00:42:44,380
There is a large and popular business
which you are causing dismay.

391
00:42:45,460 --> 00:42:50,220
Why don't you just cross the street
and let things take their course?

392
00:42:50,430 --> 00:42:53,430
Would you come in here, please?

393
00:42:57,770 --> 00:43:02,600
In Roman times, when a fellow tried
to bribe a public official,

394
00:43:02,810 --> 00:43:05,020
they would cut off his nose,
sew him in a bag

395
00:43:05,230 --> 00:43:08,860
with a wild animal,
and throw that bag in the river.

396
00:43:09,070 --> 00:43:13,450
You tell your master
that we must agree to...disagree!

397
00:43:14,910 --> 00:43:18,120
- You're making a mistake.
- I'm beginning to enjoy my mistakes.

398
00:43:18,330 --> 00:43:22,920
You fellows are 'untouchable'
is that it? No one can get to you?

399
00:43:23,120 --> 00:43:26,500
You tell Capone...
that I'll see him in hell.

400
00:43:29,710 --> 00:43:31,720
Hey! Nice house!

401
00:43:31,930 --> 00:43:34,760
I said, nice house!
Do you live there?

402
00:43:36,430 --> 00:43:40,060
Little girl's havin' a birthday, huh?

403
00:43:40,270 --> 00:43:42,230
Yes.

404
00:43:42,440 --> 00:43:44,690
Nice to have a family.

405
00:43:47,400 --> 00:43:50,110
Yes, it is.

406
00:43:50,320 --> 00:43:54,820
A man should take care,
see that nothin' happens to them.

407
00:44:09,800 --> 00:44:11,760
Catherine?!

408
00:44:13,260 --> 00:44:15,140
Catherine!

409
00:44:15,340 --> 00:44:17,800
- Where's the baby?
- She's upstairs. Eliot!

410
00:44:30,650 --> 00:44:34,360
- What were you doing up?
- I had to finish my ironing.

411
00:44:34,570 --> 00:44:39,620
You did? You're gonna come
with Daddy now, okay?

412
00:44:51,380 --> 00:44:53,800
Eliot? Okay, it's all right!

413
00:44:54,010 --> 00:44:56,300
Okay, let's go.

414
00:44:56,510 --> 00:45:00,310
Stay there!
Keep your eye on the street!

415
00:45:02,060 --> 00:45:05,600
- Where's Malone?
- On the stake-out. He'll be here.

416
00:45:05,810 --> 00:45:09,190
- Who's this guy?
- He's on Malone's list. He's okay.

417
00:45:10,650 --> 00:45:15,200
Drive to the station. She'll let you
know where to go when you get there.

418
00:45:15,400 --> 00:45:17,660
Take off your hat.

419
00:45:17,860 --> 00:45:21,200
Anything happens, shoot first.
You understand me?

420
00:45:21,410 --> 00:45:23,620
Yes, Mr Ness.

421
00:45:26,920 --> 00:45:28,580
Kiss.

422
00:45:28,790 --> 00:45:31,920
- Eskimo and butterfly, Dad.
- Okay.

423
00:45:35,470 --> 00:45:37,510
Now, go!

424
00:45:59,570 --> 00:46:01,240
Malone!

425
00:46:02,330 --> 00:46:03,790
- Are they okay?
- Yeah.

426
00:46:03,990 --> 00:46:07,370
- You sure the cop's okay?
- He'd better be, he's my cousin.

427
00:46:07,580 --> 00:46:10,790
I want to hurt the man, Malone!
You hear me?!

428
00:46:11,000 --> 00:46:13,960
I want to take the battle to him.
I want to hurt Capone.

429
00:46:14,170 --> 00:46:17,670
Well, then, a Merry Christmas,
we've got some great news.

430
00:46:17,880 --> 00:46:20,340
A huge international
shipment's coming.

431
00:46:20,550 --> 00:46:25,140
We've got the time, the place
and the whole shebang.

432
00:46:25,350 --> 00:46:28,440
Well, what are we doin'
standin' here, then?

433
00:46:29,520 --> 00:46:31,520
How do you come by this information?

434
00:46:31,730 --> 00:46:33,860
That's the second rule
of police work:

435
00:46:34,070 --> 00:46:36,820
if you want to keep a secret,
don't tell the boss.

436
00:46:42,530 --> 00:46:45,370
You know he's making
over $3 million a year?

437
00:46:45,580 --> 00:46:48,160
But he's paid no taxes,
nothing's in his name.

438
00:46:48,370 --> 00:46:50,620
If we can establish
any payments to him,

439
00:46:50,830 --> 00:46:53,880
we can prosecute him
for income tax evasion.

440
00:46:54,090 --> 00:46:55,420
What?

441
00:46:55,630 --> 00:46:59,970
I said, we can prosecute him
for income tax evasion!

442
00:47:00,180 --> 00:47:03,510
Try a murderer
for not paying his taxes?!

443
00:47:03,720 --> 00:47:06,770
Well, it's better than nothing.

444
00:47:06,970 --> 00:47:10,980
All right. How do we
link him to the money?

445
00:47:12,060 --> 00:47:14,110
I don't know.

446
00:47:15,730 --> 00:47:18,230
Go to sleep, Oscar.

447
00:48:04,950 --> 00:48:08,160
A convoy of 5-10 trucks
with good Canadian whiskey

448
00:48:08,370 --> 00:48:12,040
will be met by a high-level member
of the Capone organisation.

449
00:48:12,250 --> 00:48:15,830
He will be bringing full payment
for the shipment in cash.

450
00:48:16,040 --> 00:48:21,920
Now, the meet is to take place just
over the border on the American side.

451
00:48:22,130 --> 00:48:25,340
We want to confiscate
the liquor and the cash.

452
00:48:25,550 --> 00:48:29,470
- Captain?
- We will await their signal.

453
00:48:29,680 --> 00:48:32,810
When they're on the road
and have given the signal,

454
00:48:33,020 --> 00:48:36,810
we will engage from
the Canadian side of the bridge.

455
00:48:37,020 --> 00:48:39,020
