Stitches and standing in the rain...

477
00:50:46,230 --> 00:50:48,450
Listen, Mr Ness...

478
00:50:50,320 --> 00:50:51,950
I had an idea.

479
00:51:47,420 --> 00:51:50,510
You all have your spare shells?

480
00:52:04,940 --> 00:52:09,530
If you have to fire,
hold low and squeeze.

481
00:52:09,730 --> 00:52:12,650
And put your man down.

482
00:52:15,160 --> 00:52:17,870
Because he'll do the same to you.

483
00:52:18,030 --> 00:52:20,290
Shoot to kill.

484
00:52:20,500 --> 00:52:24,830
- Did you hear what I said?
- Yes, I did. Shoot to kill.

485
00:52:26,420 --> 00:52:28,880
Let's go.

486
00:52:52,360 --> 00:52:53,740
Easy...

487
00:52:53,950 --> 00:52:57,570
The Canadians will not show
until I flash the badge.

488
00:52:57,780 --> 00:53:01,370
So we must cover the ground
to the bridge as quickly as possible.

489
00:53:01,580 --> 00:53:03,290
George, the count's right.

490
00:53:03,500 --> 00:53:06,790
I'm concerned about
the size of these barrels!

491
00:53:07,000 --> 00:53:09,710
Malone, you and I will
take the men...

492
00:53:09,880 --> 00:53:12,800
Move it! Move it, Georgie!

493
00:53:13,010 --> 00:53:16,510
Get over here!
Leave the stuff in the cars!

494
00:53:17,470 --> 00:53:18,800
Charge!

495
00:53:21,010 --> 00:53:22,930
What the hell!
You got to die of somethin'

496
00:53:26,230 --> 00:53:30,190
- Look! Here they come!
- Mounties! Let's get out of here!

497
00:53:30,400 --> 00:53:32,360
Move, move!

498
00:53:41,870 --> 00:53:44,200
Let's go!

499
00:53:48,540 --> 00:53:49,880
I can't believe it!

500
00:53:50,090 --> 00:53:53,130
- Here are the codes.
- Give me that.

501
00:53:53,340 --> 00:53:55,130
Don't let those cars off the bridge!

502
00:54:13,980 --> 00:54:15,860
Stone, take the first car!

503
00:54:17,570 --> 00:54:20,030
Get this shit out of the way!

504
00:54:39,680 --> 00:54:41,050
Tough guy!

505
00:54:44,390 --> 00:54:46,020
Stone!

506
00:54:46,220 --> 00:54:47,600
Go!

507
00:54:49,350 --> 00:54:51,270
Stone!

508
00:54:52,360 --> 00:54:53,690
I'm okay.

509
00:54:55,230 --> 00:54:57,280
You thugs!

510
00:55:11,460 --> 00:55:13,710
You all right?

511
00:55:13,920 --> 00:55:16,800
Yeah. There he is! Go get him!

512
00:55:29,430 --> 00:55:33,520
All right!
Enough of this running shit!

513
00:55:33,730 --> 00:55:37,440
Well, Georgie-boy!
Well, what have we got here?

514
00:55:38,570 --> 00:55:40,650
Hello.

515
00:57:02,780 --> 00:57:04,240
All right! Drop the gun!

516
00:57:04,450 --> 00:57:06,950
Put your hands in the air,
you're under arrest.

517
00:57:08,030 --> 00:57:10,080
I said, drop it!

518
00:57:11,950 --> 00:57:13,500
Stop!

519
00:57:18,500 --> 00:57:21,760
God, didn't ya hear what I said?!

520
00:57:21,960 --> 00:57:24,130
What are you, deaf?!

521
00:57:25,380 --> 00:57:27,430
What is this, a game?!

522
00:57:53,120 --> 00:57:55,460
Here. Sit down.

523
00:58:04,210 --> 00:58:06,930
Stone's gonna be all right.

524
00:58:07,130 --> 00:58:10,100
I got the fellow with the satchel.

525
00:58:16,730 --> 00:58:19,100
- I had to kill him.
- Oh, yeah.

526
00:58:19,310 --> 00:58:22,150
He's as dead as Julius Caesar.

527
00:58:23,480 --> 00:58:27,150
- Would you rather it was you?
- No, I would not.

528
00:58:27,360 --> 00:58:31,950
Well, then you've done your duty.
Go home and sleep well tonight.

529
00:58:32,160 --> 00:58:35,410
The things you see
when you're out without your gun.

530
00:58:35,620 --> 00:58:39,290
Now you're a long way
from the Southside, George.

531
00:58:39,500 --> 00:58:43,170
I'm talkin' to you. Did you come
here to open a shooting gallery?

532
00:58:43,380 --> 00:58:46,760
I want you to write down the names
of your superiors and contacts.

533
00:58:46,970 --> 00:58:49,970
Why don't you kiss my ass?

534
00:58:50,180 --> 00:58:52,390
- Perhaps you didn't hear me.
- Eliot?

535
00:58:52,600 --> 00:58:54,680
- You've broken the law...
- Eliot!

536
00:58:54,890 --> 00:58:56,930
You can be tough in Leavenworth
for 30 years.

537
00:58:57,140 --> 00:59:00,190
- You're going inside for all day!
- Is that what you want?

538
00:59:00,400 --> 00:59:03,150
- Eliot!
- What?!

539
00:59:03,360 --> 00:59:05,730
Look at this!

540
00:59:05,940 --> 00:59:08,780
- Look at this!
- What is this?

541
00:59:10,990 --> 00:59:12,820
What is this?

542
00:59:13,580 --> 00:59:17,370
You got a lot of money changing
hands in this book.

543
00:59:17,580 --> 00:59:21,830
What is this, 'war'?
And 'police precincts'

544
00:59:23,500 --> 00:59:26,840
And you got a heading here...
'Circuit Court'

545
00:59:27,050 --> 00:59:30,720
You got a heading here,
'Circuit Court' What is this?

546
00:59:30,930 --> 00:59:33,890
Nothin' There's nothin'
you can make out of it.

547
00:59:34,100 --> 00:59:37,430
If any of these coded entries
indicate payment to Capone,

548
00:59:37,640 --> 00:59:39,430
then we can put Capone away.

549
00:59:39,640 --> 00:59:43,360
- Which entry is Al Capone?
- A. Costa, is that his code name?

550
00:59:43,560 --> 00:59:46,320
You'll do the whole thing
in the joint unless you help us.

551
00:59:46,520 --> 00:59:48,990
Translate this ledger for us!

552
00:59:49,190 --> 00:59:50,740
- In hell.
- In hell?!

553
00:59:52,110 --> 00:59:55,700
You will hang high
unless you cooperate.

554
00:59:55,910 --> 00:59:59,540
This man can finger Al Capone,
put him behind bars.

555
00:59:59,750 --> 01:00:01,500
Why don't you guys just fuck off?!

556
01:00:04,040 --> 01:00:08,340
I'm not fuckin' with you! We'll have
that information one way or another.

557
01:00:08,550 --> 01:00:10,470
- Not that way. Out.
- You're gonna talk!

558
01:00:10,670 --> 01:00:13,470
You're gonna be beggin' to talk!

559
01:00:13,680 --> 01:00:16,760
- You dirty son-of-a-bitch!
- Enough out of you.

560
01:00:20,430 --> 01:00:22,730
Hey, come on, you, on your feet!

561
01:00:22,940 --> 01:00:26,270
I need you to help me
to translate this book!

562
01:00:26,480 --> 01:00:28,480
I'm not gonna ask you a second time.

563
01:00:28,690 --> 01:00:30,860
I'm gonna count to three.

564
01:00:32,780 --> 01:00:36,320
What's the matter? Can't you talk
with a gun in your mouth?

565
01:00:38,410 --> 01:00:39,740
One.

566
01:00:44,000 --> 01:00:45,880
Two!

567
01:00:47,840 --> 01:00:49,340
Three.

568
01:00:50,420 --> 01:00:51,880
I'm gonna talk!

569
01:00:52,090 --> 01:00:56,680
Don't ! I'm gonna tell ya whatever
ya want. What do ya want to know?

570
01:00:59,810 --> 01:01:03,560
Now, don't let him clean himself
until after he talks.

571
01:01:03,770 --> 01:01:06,810
Now, ask him what you want to know.

572
01:01:07,020 --> 01:01:11,190
All right... Okay, I want to know
the name of the bookkeeper.

573
01:01:11,400 --> 01:01:15,530
I want a complete translation
of the code. I want a complete...

574
01:01:15,740 --> 01:01:18,240
Mister Ness!

575
01:01:24,330 --> 01:01:26,630
I do not approve of your methods!

576
01:01:27,790 --> 01:01:32,510
Yeah? Well, you're not from Chicago.

577
01:01:36,680 --> 01:01:38,970
- What?
- They got the shipment.

578
01:01:39,180 --> 01:01:41,720
- What?!
- They got the whole shipment.

579
01:01:41,930 --> 01:01:45,890
- I want that son-of-a-bitch dead!
- We're trying to locate...

580
01:01:46,100 --> 01:01:52,030
What am I, alone in this world? Did I
ask you what you're tryin' to do?

581
01:01:52,230 --> 01:01:56,820
I want you to get this fuck where he
breathes! I want Eliot Ness dead!

582
01:01:57,030 --> 01:02:00,240
I want his family dead,
his house burnt to the ground!

583
01:02:00,450 --> 01:02:02,740
I want to piss on his ashes!

584
01:02:02,950 --> 01:02:08,210
Look at this guy, this guy,
he's so serious.

585
01:02:08,420 --> 01:02:11,670
- Well, he's got a lot on his mind.
- He does?

586
01:02:11,880 --> 01:02:13,840
- Yes.
- Like what?

587
01:02:15,380 --> 01:02:17,050
Like what his name is.

588
01:02:17,260 --> 01:02:21,430
John, I thought that was all settled.
I thought we liked John.

589
01:02:21,640 --> 01:02:24,140
I suppose his middle name
will be Law.

590
01:02:24,890 --> 01:02:28,230
No...it'll be Edgar.

591
01:02:29,730 --> 01:02:33,320
- It'll be J. Edgar...
- I don't think so.

592
01:02:36,900 --> 01:02:39,280
God, you're beautiful.

593
01:02:41,120 --> 01:02:43,370
You should have seen us last night.

594
01:02:45,410 --> 01:02:48,580
I know. I should have been here.
I wanted to be here.

595
01:02:48,790 --> 01:02:52,040
I know. I understand, I do.

596
01:02:53,590 --> 01:02:56,460
Just tell me, are you being careful?

597
01:02:56,670 --> 01:03:00,180
- Careful as mice.
- Are you making progress?

598
01:03:00,390 --> 01:03:02,550
- Progress?
- Yes?

599
01:03:02,760 --> 01:03:06,930
Mrs Ness, I think your husband
just became the man who got Al Capone.

600
01:03:15,570 --> 01:03:20,070
Gentlemen! A subpoena was issued
for Alphonse Capone

601
01:03:20,280 --> 01:03:25,200
by my office this morning,
for the crime of evading

602
01:03:25,410 --> 01:03:28,960
and conspiring to evade
Federal Income Tax.

603
01:03:29,160 --> 01:03:32,290
- What's the maximum he could get?
- If convicted on all counts,

604
01:03:32,500 --> 01:03:36,590
Mr Capone could have
up to 28 years.

605
01:03:36,800 --> 01:03:39,970
Excuse me, that's all. Thank you.

606
01:03:46,510 --> 01:03:50,810
The car's in the yard. When ya get
him there, don't answer the phone.

607
01:03:51,020 --> 01:03:53,150
- We'll call, let it ring...
- Twice.

608
01:03:53,360 --> 01:03:55,270
- We'll call...
- From the corner.

609
01:03:55,480 --> 01:03:59,070
- Anybody knocks on the door...
- Come out shooting. I got it.

610
01:03:59,280 --> 01:04:02,280
You enjoy the tactical aspects
of law enforcement, Oscar?

611
01:04:02,490 --> 01:04:05,280
Much more diverting
than accounting.

612
01:04:05,490 --> 01:04:07,660
I'm bein' good to you,
you got to be good to me.

613
01:04:07,870 --> 01:04:11,330
We made a deal,
we're gonna stick to it, okay?

614
01:04:16,750 --> 01:04:19,760
Oh, yes, much more diverting
than accounting.

615
01:04:19,970 --> 01:04:22,220
Okay, we see yous tonight.

616
01:04:22,430 --> 01:04:26,180
All right, all the way down
and no stops.

617
01:04:34,230 --> 01:04:37,940
...he's been saying,
"I will speak up."

618
01:04:39,730 --> 01:04:43,860
For which I must commend
the excellent work

619
01:04:44,070 --> 01:04:47,740
of Eliot Ness
and his squad of Untouchables.

620
01:04:50,330 --> 01:04:52,710
- What was it, a boy or a girl?
- Boy.

621
01:04:52,910 --> 01:04:55,880
- Congratulations! What's his name?
- John.

622
01:04:56,080 --> 01:04:59,050
- John?
- Yeah. John James.

623
01:05:00,260 --> 01:05:02,630
- So she's okay?
- Yeah, she's okay.

624
01:05:02,840 --> 01:05:06,300
In fact, when she gets out,
she wants to repaint the house.

625
01:05:06,510 --> 01:05:10,850
Then she'll find the house too small,
you'll have to move.

626
01:05:11,060 --> 01:05:16,350
- Goodness, it's nice to be married.
- If you can stand the pain.

627
01:05:16,560 --> 01:05:18,150
Mr Burns, where's Mr Wallace?

628
01:05:18,360 --> 01:05:23,860
Didn't you see him? He just went
down in the service elevator.

629
01:05:24,860 --> 01:05:28,910
- You keep an eye out at all times...
- Take it easy, we'll be fine.

630
01:05:29,120 --> 01:05:31,580
They are going to...

631
01:05:39,710 --> 01:05:42,960
- Did he say the service elevator?
- Yes.

632
01:05:49,100 --> 01:05:52,470
- Wallace! Wallace!
- Here, let's take the stairs.

633
01:06:32,470 --> 01:06:34,810
Oh, no.

634
01:06:35,890 --> 01:06:38,980
- No, no!
- Easy... Easy!

635
01:06:41,520 --> 01:06:43,020
Oscar.

636
01:07:22,020 --> 01:07:24,270
Oh, Jesus.

637
01:07:27,990 --> 01:07:30,780
You gonna be all right?

638
01:07:50,880 --> 01:07:56,060
It's always a crime when a young guy
goes down in the line, Jimmy.

639
01:07:57,140 --> 01:08:00,270
I'd hate to see it happen
to someone I know.

640
01:08:00,480 --> 01:08:04,110
Sometimes it's better
not to get involved.

641
01:08:04,310 --> 01:08:06,440
Jimmy!

642
01:08:06,650 --> 01:08:10,320
Take a day off.
Get out of the city for a while.

643
01:08:10,530 --> 01:08:12,570
You know what I mean?

644
01:08:29,670 --> 01:08:31,590
- Al Capone.
- We have no Mr Capone...

645
01:08:31,800 --> 01:08:35,300
- I know, get him.
- We have no Mr Capone...

646
01:08:35,760 --> 01:08:37,390
I said...

647
01:08:44,020 --> 01:08:47,320
- Something you want here?
- My friend was killed today.

648
01:08:47,520 --> 01:08:50,280
- I don't care.
- You don't care.

649
01:08:53,200 --> 01:08:55,490
Now he does.

650
01:08:55,700 --> 01:09:00,040
Come on here, Capone. You want
to fight? You and me, right here?

651
01:09:00,250 --> 01:09:01,580
That's it, come on!

652
01:09:01,790 --> 01:09:05,380
You afraid to come out from behind
your men, to stand up for yourself?

653
01:09:05,580 --> 01:09:09,590
- You want to do the mat now?
- Yeah! Come on, you son-of-a-bitch!

654
01:09:09,800 --> 01:09:11,670
- What?
- Easy.

655
01:09:11,880 --> 01:09:15,430
You talk to me like that in front
of my son? Fuck you and your family!

656
01:09:18,180 --> 01:09:21,390
Easy. It's me. It's me!

657
01:09:21,600 --> 01:09:23,310
Not this way.

658
01:09:23,520 --> 01:09:26,230
You fuck, you got nothin'
You're nothin' but talk and a badge.

659
01:09:26,400 --> 01:09:32,110
You're here because you got nothin'
in court, no bookkeeper, nothin'

660
01:09:32,320 --> 01:09:36,700
If you were a man, you would've done
it now! You got nothin' you punk!

661
01:09:46,120 --> 01:09:49,170
Well, no, I understand.

662
01:09:49,380 --> 01:09:52,260
Believe me, I understand.

663
01:09:59,680 --> 01:10:02,060
Well, what's happened?

664
01:10:03,520 --> 01:10:08,150
He says he can't be unprotected.

665
01:10:09,900 --> 01:10:12,610
What is it that the guy says?

666
01:10:12,780 --> 01:10:15,400
He says he won't make
a fool out of himself,

667
01:10:15,610 --> 01:10:18,950
and he won't go into court
without a witness.

668
01:10:19,160 --> 01:10:23,410
So tomorrow morning the D.A. will
announce that he's dropping the case.

669
01:10:23,620 --> 01:10:27,500
- He's gonna give up.
- He won't do it without a witness.

670
01:10:27,710 --> 01:10:30,420
We have Wallace's files
and the ledgers.

671
01:10:30,590 --> 01:10:34,260
There's a time when I think
you have to cut your losses.

672
01:10:35,340 --> 01:10:37,380
Hello?

673
01:10:39,430 --> 01:10:41,470
Hello.

674
01:10:43,060 --> 01:10:45,100
Yes.

675
01:10:48,400 --> 01:10:51,310
No, he didn't have a family.

676
01:10:53,780 --> 01:10:56,490
How is everything there?

677
01:10:59,740 --> 01:11:03,240
No, you do it however you want.

678
01:11:05,290 --> 01:11:07,540
I promise I will.

679
01:11:08,620 --> 01:11:10,960
You give her my love.

680
01:11:11,170 --> 01:11:13,210
I love you, too.

681
01:11:15,340 --> 01:11:20,510
Mr Ness, we got a ledger here listing
payments to Chicago City officials.

682
01:11:20,720 --> 01:11:24,680
- We got Al Capone, Frank Nitti...
- I think that's enough for today.

683
01:11:24,890 --> 01:11:28,940
- If we don't stay on top...
- That'll do. Thank you.

684
01:11:29,140 --> 01:11:33,060
I'd like to request to stick around.

685
01:11:34,230 --> 01:11:36,820
- We got to bust these guys.
- I know we got to.

686
01:11:45,700 --> 01:11:47,790
Is that it?

687
01:11:48,870 --> 01:11:51,500
- I'm sorry?
- You heard me.

688
01:11:51,710 --> 01:11:54,170
My question is, are we done?

689
01:11:56,170 --> 01:11:58,550
Yes, I think we're done.

690
01:11:58,760 --> 01:12:01,640
So we sat in at a game
that was above our head?

691
01:12:01,840 --> 01:12:04,220
It appears so.
It appears so to Mr Wallace.

692
01:12:04,430 --> 01:12:06,720
He's dead! And the D.A.
is gonna drop the case!

693
01:12:06,930 --> 01:12:09,230
He will not go into court
without a witness

694
01:12:09,430 --> 01:12:12,400
and without Capone's bookkeeper,
Walter Payne.

695
01:12:12,600 --> 01:12:17,440
- What are you prepared to do now?
- What would you have me do?

696
01:12:17,650 --> 01:12:20,400
I have taken this
as far as it can go.

697
01:12:34,420 --> 01:12:38,510
- What did your wife want?
- She wanted to know if I was...

698
01:12:39,590 --> 01:12:42,380
- My wife?
- Yeah.

699
01:12:46,350 --> 01:12:49,220
She wanted to know
if I was all right.

700
01:12:51,560 --> 01:12:53,900
It's nice being married, eh?

701
01:12:55,150 --> 01:12:56,480
Yes.

702
01:12:56,690 --> 01:12:59,990
She's sitting in some room surrounded
by people she doesn't know,

703
01:13:00,190 --> 01:13:04,490
going over...
kitchen colour charts or something.

704
01:13:11,120 --> 01:13:16,840
Some part of the world still cares
what colour the kitchen is.

705
01:13:21,380 --> 01:13:25,680
Eliot, I want you to do
one more thing for me.

706
01:13:28,100 --> 01:13:31,640
Get back to the D.A. and stall him.

707
01:13:32,350 --> 01:13:36,520
- Wait a minute, stall him with what?
- Just do as I say.

708
01:13:39,940 --> 01:13:42,360
I think I know how to find this guy.

709
01:13:44,450 --> 01:13:47,200
Walter?

710
01:13:47,410 --> 01:13:52,410
Al says we got to get out of town
until he can fix this subpoena thing.

711
01:13:52,620 --> 01:13:55,540
We're leavin' tonight.

712
01:13:58,380 --> 01:14:00,920
Two ball, down.

713
01:14:05,300 --> 01:14:08,010
Mike, you got a minute?

714
01:14:08,180 --> 01:14:10,890
I do now, don't I?

715
01:14:11,970 --> 01:14:15,270
And what are you doin'
in a club for cops, Jimmy?

716
01:14:16,230 --> 01:14:18,810
This is a place for cops.

717
01:14:19,020 --> 01:14:21,610
Can we step outside?

718
01:14:21,820 --> 01:14:26,150
All right, all right,
but I got nothin' to say to ya.

719
01:14:30,450 --> 01:14:35,910
